/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:15:The comparator is also too weak. Naming the `killed neutral-Eulerian package` is useful for local bookkeeping, but beating an already rejected package is not evidence of theorem relevance. The real comparator should be the closest live geometric prior art, especially Constantin-Fefferman style direction-control frameworks. Otherwise the chain can report progress while only outperforming a strawman that the portfolio has already discarded.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:25:There is also a hidden mismatch problem. `Local Beltrami deficit`, `direction coherence`, and `Beltrami-plus-concentration` are not interchangeable currencies, and neither are `Constantin-Fefferman-type criterion` and `one fixed full-stretching target`. Some pairings are much more natural than others. The step never requires the chain to justify why the chosen observable is even in the right currency for the chosen endpoint. It only requires a table.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:53:Benchmarking against the `neutral-Eulerian comparator` and `closest Constantin-Fefferman-type prior art` is necessary, but the order is wrong. Prior-art comparison should have been present in Step 1, not introduced only after a preferred geometry package and observable have already been selected. Otherwise the chain is structurally biased toward rediscovering known direction-regularity logic with nicer packaging.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-010/attacks/chain-01.md:75:Third, the prior-art overlap risk is extreme. `Direction coherence`, `local Beltrami deficit`, `tube persistence`, and a bridge to `Constantin-Fefferman-type criterion` are already living inside a mature geometric-depletion neighborhood. If the novelty is just an adapted package that tracks geometry more sympathetically, the route is probably re-encoding the old insight that aligned vorticity weakens stretching, while inheriting the same old blockage: maintaining and exploiting that alignment at the right scale without paying prohibitive derivative or localization debt.
