/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-010/judgments/chain-01.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The selected chain has two real strengths: it is unusually honest about localization debt, and it correctly identifies full stretching contact as the decisive battleground. But it still gives geometry too much procedural sympathy. Too much of Steps 1 through 4 can be completed with package selection, observable screening, and narrative accounting before the branch is forced to write down a serious theorem-facing proposition.
