+# The Live Geometry Claim Is Only Proxy-Admissible Via The Neutral-Eulerian Intense-Set Coherence/Persistence Class
+
+Status: `INFERRED` Step-015 admissibility freeze with `VERIFIED` support
+
+The inherited theorem floor for this mission still remains the suitable-weak /
+Leray-Hopf plus LEI package. On the current local record, the geometry branch
+does not have a directly theorem-floor-native positive mechanism on that floor.
+
+What survives instead is narrower:
+
+- standalone direction coherence remains stretching-facing, but only as a
+  dynamically weak comparator under the fixed neutral Eulerian package;
+- standalone tube persistence remains live only as a dynamic ingredient and
+  collapses to descriptive geometry once fixed-package auditing forbids hidden
+  relocalization;
+- so the only honest live Step-015 candidate statement is proxy-based rather
+  than theorem-floor admissible.
+
+The proxy class frozen by the Step-015 report is:
+
+`neutral-Eulerian intense-set coherence/persistence class`
+
+meaning the thresholded intense set together with a hoped-for coherent tube
+family whose direction coherence persists across the diffusion-scale `r^2`
+window.
+
+This is the reusable admissibility outcome for the geometry branch: if the
+branch is kept alive at all, it must now be described as living on that proxy
+class rather than as already native to the inherited theorem floor.
+
+Filed from:
+- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-015-exploration-002-admissibility-comparator-and-verdict.md`
