+# The Geometry Branch Fails At The Theorem-Floor Bridge Gate Before Package Selection
+
+Status: `INFERRED` Step-015 branch-stop verdict with `VERIFIED` support
+
+Once the Step-015 admissibility decision is frozen as proxy-based, the next
+question is not package optimization. It is whether the proxy class has a
+cheaper-than-theorem bridge back to the inherited suitable-weak / LEI floor.
+
+The local record does not supply such a bridge. The exact burden already has
+three inseparable parts:
+
+- match coherent intense components across the full diffusion-scale `r^2`
+  window inside the neutral Eulerian package, without hidden relocalization,
+  threshold retuning, or axis fitting;
+- propagate direction coherence on that moving intense set without importing
+  the stronger `nabla xi`-type derivative control that collapses back into the
+  known direction-regularity comparator;
+- and convert the proxy persistence/coherence information into a genuinely
+  smaller criterion-scale direction input or a smaller full-stretching
+  contribution on the inherited theorem floor.
+
+Those are not later technicalities. The existing geometry audit already names
+their components as the missing mechanism behind the hybrid's failure:
+Eulerian component matching, diffusion-scale persistence, forbidden
+relocalization, and `nabla xi` debt.
+
+So the honest Step-015 verdict is:
+
+`theorem-floor obstruction, branch should stop before package selection`
+
+The bridge burden already looks theorem-scale rather than cheaper than the
+target theorem, which is why this obstruction label comes earlier than any
+further packaging choice.
+
+Filed from:
